<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870717-0147 </DOCNO><HL> Financing Business:Cleveland Electric Illuminating Co.</HL><DD> 07/17/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> CXSTOCK MARKET, OFFERINGS (STK) </IN><TEXT>   CLEVELAND ELECTRIC ILLUMINATING CO., a unit of Centerior Energy Corp., said it sold 750 shares of its serial preferred, remarketed as Series P, at $100,000 each. The utility said the stock will have an initial dividend rate of 8%, payable Sept. 23. The rate will be reset periodically thereafter. The company said proceeds will be used for construction and for general purposes. The underwriter is Merrill Lynch Capital Markets. </TEXT></DOC>